"point_demo_real_world.mst — like point_demo.mst, but loaded against the
 REAL world/world.list (sprint_s06_detail.md step 6: 'point_demo.mst now
 prints via printString'). point_demo.mst itself stays untouched — it's
 also exercised with NO world loaded at all (it_cli.rs's world_missing),
 which this variant can't be since it needs Transcript/printString/+.

 Uses the REAL world Point class (world/28_point.mst) rather than a
 throwaway stand-in of its own — this file used to define its own
 `Object subclass: Point [...]`, which predates 28_point.mst being added
 to the base world and started tripping 'cannot change shape of existing
 class Point' once both existed (found 2026-07-08). The real Point's own
 constructor is `x:y:`, not `new` + `setX:y:`, and its `printOn:` uses
 `@` (`x@y`), not a parenthesized pair — this file now exercises exactly
 that real API instead of shadowing it."

P1 := Point x: 1 y: 2.
Transcript show: 'Point creation ok'; cr.
P2 := Point x: 3 y: 4.
P3 := P1 + P2.
Transcript show: 'Point + ok'; cr.
Transcript show: P3 printString; cr.
